Patch Set 2:

@zhiyan

> What about to add task_update, task_get and task_delete as well?

I think you're right that to get the full set of tasks stuff working correctly with the v2 registry that will be required.

I'm not being that ambitious here ... the focus of this patch is more a bugfix -- just to remove a barrier to running the v2 functional tests when the registry is enabled.

I think probably a good set of steps would be:

1) merge this ;-)
2) get the v2 tests running with and without the registry
3) add the remaining tasks functions and ensure there are also functional tests which exercise them

I'm in two minds about (2). I have a small local patch which changes running the v2 tests to use the registry. I could extend that to make the v2 functional tests run both registry and non-registry, but I think there's a push to get some of the functional tests in tempest, so I'm not sure what the best approach is there.
